definition.value: A linear amino pentasaccharide comprising D-glucose at the reducing end with a beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactosyl moiety at the 4-position.
An L-lysinium residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position 5 (the 5S stereoisomer); major microspecies at pH 7.3.
An L-isoleucine residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position 4 (the 3R,4S diastereoisomer).
An L-glutamate residue that is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A branched amino octasaccharide comprising a linear hexasaccharide of beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, alpha-D-galactose, beta-D-galactose and D-glucose residues linked sequentially (1->4), (1->6), (1->3), (1->4) and (1->4), to the GlcNac and GalNAc residues of which are also (1->3) linked alpha-L-galactose and beta-D-galactose residues respectively.
A 3-hydroxy-L-aspartate residue in which the carbon bearing the alcoholic hydroxy group (position 3) has R-configuration.; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A glycooctaosylceramide having an beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->3)]-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)-[beta-D-Gal-(1->3)]-beta-D-GalNAc-(1->3)-alpha-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)--D-Glcp component attached to the primary hydroxy function of a ceramide with a d18:1 sphingoid base and an undefined fatty acyl chain.

A sesquiterpenoid that is (S)-beta-macrocarpene in which a hydrogen of the methyl group that is attached to a double bond has been replaced by a hydroxy group. The first step in the biosynthesis of the sesquiterpene phytoalexin zealexin A1 from (S)-beta-macrocarpene in maize.

A sesquiterpenoid that is (S)-beta-macrocarpen-15-ol in which the hydroxy group has been oxidised to an aldehyde group. The second step in the biosynthesis of the sesquiterpene phytoalexin zealexin A1 from (S)-beta-macrocarpene in maize.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting forom the deprotonation of the carboxy group of zealexin A1. The major speciess at pH 7.3.
An L-asparagine residue that is substituted by an hydroxy group at position 3 (the 3R stereoisomer).
An L-argininium residue that is substituted by a hydroxy group at position 4; major microspecies at pH 7.3.
A monoterpenoid indole alkaloid with formula C21H24N2O3, isolated from Vinca sardoa and Uncaria rhynchophylla.
